>\n<ul>\n<li>Thief<\/li>\n<li>Play Rough<\/li>\n<li>Fake Out<\/li>\n<li>Pursuit<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Knock Off<\/li>\n<li>Psycho Cut<\/li>\n<li>Feint<\/li>\n<li>Pursuit<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Punishment<\/li>\n<li>Ice Shard<\/li>\n<li>Swagger<\/li>\n<li>Fake Out<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Punishment<\/li>\n<li>Air Cutter<\/li>\n<li>Night Shade<\/li>\n<li>Swagger<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<\/div>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\">\n<table class=\"table grey left aligntop collapsed\" style=\"min-width:500px;\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"6\" class=\"text-large left\">Gym Leader V\u00e9ga (Insane)<br \/>\n        <span class=\"table-toggle\"><a href=\"#\" class=\"toggle-link\">[show]<\/a><\/span>\n        <\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<\/thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th><\/th>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/sprites\/pokemon\/liepard.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/sprites\/pokemon\/absol.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/sprites\/pokemon\/spiritomb.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/sprites\/pokemon\/honchkrow.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/sprites\/pokemon\/pawniard.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Pokemon<\/th>\n<td>Liepard Lv. 26<\/td>\n<td>Absol Lv. 27<\/td>\n<td>Spiritomb Lv. 27<\/td>\n<td>Honchkrow Lv. 26<\/td>\n<td>Pawniard Lv. 26<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Type<\/th>\n<td>Dark<\/td>\n<td>Dark<\/td>\n<td>Ghost \/ Dark<\/td>\n<td>Dark \/ Flying<\/td>\n<td>Dark \/ Steel<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Weaknesses<\/th>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Fighting (2x)<\/li>\n<li>Bug (2x)<\/li>\n<li>Fairy (2x)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Fighting (2x)<\/li>\n<li>Bug (2x)<\/li>\n<li>Fairy (2x)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Fairy (2x)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Rock (2x)<\/li>\n<li>Electric (2x)<\/li>\n<li>Ice (2x)<\/li>\n<li>Fairy (2x)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Fighting (4x)<\/li>\n<li>Fire (2x)<\/li>\n<li>Ground (2x)<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Held Item<\/th>\n<td>Focus Sash<\/td>\n<td>Absolite<\/td>\n<td>Leftovers<\/td>\n<td>Big Root<\/td>\n<td>Eviolite<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Moves<\/th>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Night Daze<\/li>\n<li>Burning Jealousy<\/li>\n<li>Fake Out<\/li>\n<li>Thunder Wave<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Knock Off<\/li>\n<li>Close Combat<\/li>\n<li>Play Rough<\/li>\n<li>Swords Dance<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Hex<\/li>\n<li>Will-O-Wisp<\/li>\n<li>Calm Mind<\/li>\n<li>Protect<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Oblivion Wing<\/li>\n<li>Heat Wave<\/li>\n<li>Protect<\/li>\n<li>Roost<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<td>\n<ul>\n<li>Iron Head<\/li>\n<li>Night Slash<\/li>\n<li>Protect<\/li>\n<li>Swords Dance<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<\/div>\n<\/div>\n<p>It is ideal to use Fighting, Bug, or Fairy-type Pok\u00e9mon as a counter to V\u00e9ga\u2019s Dark-types.<\/p>\n<h2>Crater Town Gym Puzzle<\/h2>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/vega\/02-pokemon-unbound-gym-entrance-crater-town-gym.jpg\" alt=\"Gym entrance \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Gym entrance<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>When entering the gym, the surroundings will be shrouded in darkness, reducing your vision. Each time you defeat a Trainer, some of your vision will be restored. Additionally, the Gym has several Trainers patrolling the area, teleporting you back to the entrance (or a checkpoint) if you\u2019re caught. <\/p>\n<div class=\"callout-box\"><strong>Tip:<\/strong> Although battles are optional, it is <em>highly recommended<\/em> to go through all Trainer battles, as solving the Gym puzzle with reduced vision is near impossible. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide on restoring your vision and reaching V\u00e9ga. <\/div>\n<p>Upon entering the gym, head towards the right and go straight up. This room contains 4 Trainers you can battle. Each battle will restore a part of your vision.<\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/vega\/03-pokemon-unbound-path-to-trainer-battles.jpg\" alt=\"Path to Trainer battles \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Path to Trainer battles<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p><strong>Step 1:<\/strong> Battle each of these trainers ahead.<\/p>\n<table class=\"table grey left even-2col img125-1stcol\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\" class=\"text-large center\">1st Battle &#8211; Youngster Dixon<\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<\/thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/vega\/04-pokemon-unbound-youngster-dixon.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/sprites\/pokemon\/nuzleaf.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Pokemon<\/th>\n<td>Nuzleaf Lv. 21<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Type<\/th>\n<td>Dark \/ Grass<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/vega\/05-pokemon-unbound-exact-location-of-youngster-dixon.jpg\" alt=\"Exact Location of Youngster Dixon \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Exact Location of Youngster Dixon<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>Going further up will lead you to the second Trainer.<\/p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\">\n<table class=\"table grey left img125-1stcol\" style=\"min-width:350px;\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"2\" class=\"text-large center\">2nd Battle &#8211; Scientist Dilweed<\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<\/thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/vega\/06-pokemon-unbound-scientist-dilweed.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/sprites\/pokemon\/poochyena.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Pokemon<\/th>\n<td>Poochyena Lv. 21<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Type<\/th>\n<td>Dark<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<\/div>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/vega\/07-pokemon-unbound-exact-locations-of-trainer-battles-2-and-3.jpg\" alt=\"Exact locations of Trainer battles 2 and 3 \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Exact locations of Trainer battles 2 and 3<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>Finally, head even further up for the final battle consisting of 2 Trainers.<\/p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\">\n<table class=\"table grey left img125-1stcol\" style=\"min-width:450px;\">\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th colspan=\"3\" class=\"text-large center\">3rd Battle &#8211; Medium Lyssa &#038; Gentleman Clemonce<\/th>\n<\/tr>\n<\/thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/vega\/08-pokemon-unbound-medium-lyssa-and-gentleman-clemonce.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/sprites\/pokemon\/murkrow.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/sprites\/pokemon\/houndour.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Pokemon<\/th>\n<td>Murkrow Lv. 21<\/td>\n<td>Houndour Lv. 21<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Type<\/th>\n<td>Dark \/ Flying<\/td>\n<td>Dark \/ Fire<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<\/div>\n<p><strong>Step 2:<\/strong> With your vision restored, head back to the gym\u2019s entrance. <\/p>\n<p>Then from there, follow the path leading straight up and towards the left. <\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/vega\/09-pokemon-unbound-heading-towards-the-1st-patrolling-trainer.jpg\" alt=\"Heading towards the first patrolling Trainer \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Heading towards the first patrolling Trainer<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p><strong>Step 3:<\/strong> Towards the end of this corridor, dodge the Trainer patrolling the area by hiding in the small space on the bottom side of the wall.<\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/vega\/10-pokemon-unbound-hiding-space-in-the-wall.jpg\" alt=\"Hiding space in the wall \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Hiding space in the wall<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p><strong>Step 4:<\/strong> Go further along the path left, hiding from the Trainer in the red headband, just as done in the previous step. <\/p>\n<p>Keep walking till you reach the end of the wall. <\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/vega\/11-pokemon-unbound-path-towards-checkpoint.jpg\" alt=\"Path towards Checkpoint \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Path towards Checkpoint<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p><strong>Step 5:<\/strong> This is a checkpoint. Being caught by subsequent Trainers will teleport you back here.<\/p>\n<p>Make your way along the straight path, dodging the three Trainers in between. <\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/vega\/12-pokemon-unbound-hiding-space-from-1st-trainer.jpg\" alt=\"Hiding space from 1st Trainer \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Hiding space from 1st Trainer<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>The hiding area for the 2nd Trainer here is quite small so be sure to time your run appropriately.<\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/vega\/13-pokemon-unbound-getting-caught-from-2nd-trainer.jpg\" alt=\"Getting caught from 2nd Trainer \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Getting caught from 2nd Trainer<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>The third Trainer\u2019s run overlaps with the second, making this dodge slightly complicated. You can hide at the very end of the corridor to avoid him, as done in the image below. However, you have to run out of here immediately, as the Trainer will catch you on his way back.<\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/vega\/14-pokemon-unbound-heading-towards-the-final-trainer.jpg\" alt=\"Heading towards the final trainer \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Heading towards the final trainer<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p><strong>Step 6:<\/strong> Make your way down &#038; over through the narrow corridor, avoiding the final Trainer with the video camera. <\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/vega\/15-pokemon-unbound-path-to-vega.jpg\" alt=\"Path to V\u00e9ga \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Path to V\u00e9ga<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p><strong>Step 7:<\/strong> Enter the open room at the end of this path to reach V\u00e9ga.<\/p>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/vega\/16-pokemon-unbound-vega-battle-room.jpg\" alt=\"V\u00e9ga battle room \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>V\u00e9ga battle room<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<h2>Tips for Defeating V\u00e9ga<\/h2>\n<p>Here are some tips that\u2019ll help you battle V\u00e9ga:<\/p>\n<p><strong>Use Dark-type Counters:<\/strong> All 3 of V\u00e9ga\u2019s Pokemon are Dark. This heavily incentivizes using Fighting, Bug, or Fairy-type Pokemon as a counter to the gym leader. His Liepard and Absol are relatively less aggressive, mostly using moves like Fake Out and Detect respectively. <\/p>\n<p>In contrast, Sneasel generally spams a mix between Quick Attack and Icy Mist, making it a greater threat. <\/p>\n<p><strong>Counter the Negative Emotions:<\/strong> The gym is filled with negative emotions which inflict roughly 6% max HP worth of damage to your active Pokemon at the end of each turn. Dark, Psychic, and Ghost-type Pokemon are immune to this effect. Additionally, any Pokemon featuring the moves Oblivious, Unaware, or Magic Guard are also protected from this debuff (regardless of the typing).<\/p>\n<p>If you\u2019re facing significant difficulties battling V\u00e9ga due to the negative emotions effect, try swapping out your Pokemon with the protected classes or learning the above-mentioned moves. <\/p>\n<h2>Pokemon Team Suggestions<\/h2>\n<p>If you\u2019re looking to catch some new Pokemon that are effective against V\u00e9ga, here are some recommended ones that can be found on nearby routes:<\/p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\">\n<table class=\"table grey left\" style=\"min-width:350px;\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<th><\/th>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/sprites\/pokemon\/yanma.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<td><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/sprites\/pokemon\/venonat.png\" alt=\"\"><\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Pokemon<\/th>\n<td>Yanma<\/td>\n<td>Venonat<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Type<\/th>\n<td>Bug \/ Flying<\/td>\n<td>Bug \/ Poison<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Location<\/th>\n<td>Route 5 (Day)<\/td>\n<td>Route 5<\/td>\n<\/tr>\n<\/tbody>\n<\/table>\n<\/div>\n<h2>Rewards<\/h2>\n<figure>\n  <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/gyms\/vega\/17-pokemon-unbound-obtaining-the-vision-badge.jpg\" alt=\"Obtaining the Vision Badge \/ Pok\u00e9mon Unbound\"><figcaption>Obtaining the Vision Badge<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n<p>Defeating V\u00e9ga rewards you with the following:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>\u20bd 3,360<\/li>\n<li><a href=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/tms-hms\/tm046-thief\/\">TM46 Thief<\/a><\/li>\n<li>Vision Badge &#8211; Makes all Pok\u00e9mon up till level 32 obey your commands. It also allows the use of <a href=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/tms-hms\/hm01-cut\/\">HM01 Cut<\/a> outside of battle, helping you cut down special trees blocking your path. <\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n        <a href=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/gyms\/\" class=\"parent-page-card\">\n            <picture class=\"card-img\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"400\" height=\"400\" src=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/exterior-crater-town-gym.jpg\" class=\"attachment-full size-full wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/exterior-crater-town-gym.jpg 400w, https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-content\/assets\/images\/2024\/12\/exterior-crater-town-gym-200x200.jpg 200w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px\" \/>\t\t\t\t            <\/picture>\n            <span class=\"card-info\">\n                <span class=\"card-info__caption\">Back to:<\/span>\n                <strong class=\"wiki-title\">Gyms<\/strong>\n            <\/span>\n        <\/a>\n\n\t\t\n","protected":false},"featured_media":2589,"parent":2584,"menu_order":2,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_acf_changed":false},"categories":[],"class_list":["post-2588","wiki","type-wiki","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry"],"acf":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/wiki\/2588","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/wiki"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/wiki"}],"up":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/wiki\/2584"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/2589"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=2588"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/unboundwiki.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=2588"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":